 Lee Joon-seok had been ordered to serve 36 years in prison for negligence and abandoning passengers aboard the Sewol , by a district court .
But this was increased to life in prison today by an appellate court convicted him of homicide by account of his ` willful negligence .
The 6,825-tonne passenger ship sank off the southwest coast on April 16 last year , killing 304 people .